PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775052666
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FArtemis is NASA's lunar exploration
OL,7,Fprogramme, during which the space
OL,8,Fagency will send astronauts on
OL,9,F"increasingly difficult missions".
OL,11,FThe program began with Artemis I, an
OL,12,Funcrewed test flight which launched
OL,13,Fthe Orion spacecraft towards the end
OL,14,Fof 2022.
OL,16,FThe second mission builds on the
OL,17,Ffirst, testing the capabilities of the
OL,18,Fnext Orion spacecraft, which is now
OL,19,Ffitted with the systems it needs to
OL,20,Fhouse a crew.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775052666
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FA rocket, which stands at 98m, will
OL,7,Flaunch the vessel from the Kennedy
OL,8,FSpace Center in Florida.
OL,10,FThe crew will then orbit the Earth
OL,11,Fmultiple times, before flying around
OL,12,Fthe Moon, and then splashing down in
OL,13,Fthe Pacific Ocean as gravity pulls
OL,14,Fthem back down.
OL,16,FDuring its course, Artemis II will
OL,17,Ftest navigation, communication and
OL,18,Flife support systems.
OL,20,FFollowing Artemis II, there are two
OL,21,Fmore Artemis missions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775052666
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FArtemis III will launch next year, and
OL,7,Fwill be designed test how the
OL,8,Fspacecraft could dock with the
OL,9,Fcommercial spacecraft needed to land
OL,10,Fastronauts on the moon.
OL,12,FArtemis IV then plans to mark
OL,13,Fhumanity's return to the lunar
OL,14,Fsurface, where two astronauts will
OL,15,Fspend approximately a week near the
OL,16,FSouth Pole of the Moon.
OL,18,FWhy is NASA sending a crew back to the
OL,19,FMoon?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775052666
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FThe Artemis mission is part of NASA's
OL,7,Flonger-term plans.
OL,9,F"We're going back to the Moon for
OL,10,Fscientific discovery, economic
OL,11,Fbenefits, and inspiration for a new
OL,12,Fgeneration of explorers", they say, as
OL,13,Fwell as to build on their foundation
OL,14,Ffor the "first crewed missions to
OL,15,FMars."
OL,17,FEventually, NASA hope to build a lunar
OL,18,Fbase on the surface of the moon, which
OL,19,Fwould allow astronauts to live and
OL,20,Fwork there.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775052666
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FWith the support of such a base, the
OL,7,Fspace agency would then be able to
OL,8,Fwork on the technology required to
OL,9,Fprotect a future Mars crew from lack
OL,10,Fof air, space radiation and extreme
OL,11,Ftemperatures.
OL,13,FThere is still significant work to be
OL,14,Fdone before these ambitions become
OL,15,Freality, but NASA sees Artemis
OL,16,Frepresenting a crucial step in that
OL,17,Fdirection.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
